  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nThe ethers OVM provider is not correctly set when running a hardhat script. A script can never get past an `await ethers.provider.ready` call.\r\n\r\nThis only happens when `ovm: true` is set.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n1. Set up a hardhat environment with the following data:\r\n```\r\n    optimism: {\r\n      url: 'https://kovan.optimism.io',\r\n      accounts: ['0x1111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111111'],\r\n      gasPrice: 0,\r\n      ovm: true\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n2. Run a script that calls `await ethers.provider.ready`.\r\n3. Observe that the code execution does not pass this line.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe provider should be `ready` by the time the script begins running.\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: macOS\r\n - Package Version (or commit hash):\r\n    - \"hardhat\": \"2.0.8\"\r\n    - \"ethers\": \"5.1.4\"\r\n    - \"@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers\": \"2.0.2\"\r\n\r\n",
